Textarea/TextInput field with "django-filebrowser-no-grappelli" support.

Usage:
-----
 *  Install "django-sakkada"
 *  Install "django-filebrowser-no-grappelli"
    (https://pypi.python.org/pypi/django-filebrowser-no-grappelli)
 *  Import "sakkada.admin.editors.simplefb.SimpleFBTextarea"
 *  Set "SimpleFBTextarea" ("SimpleFBInput") as widget of desired fields
 *  Copy static "admin/*" and "filebrowser/js/FB_FileBrowseField.js"
    (to override default "FB_FileBrowseField.js") to your project static folder
    or add "sakkada.admin.editors.simplefb" to your INSTALLED_APPS before
    "filebrowser".
 *  Look at "jquery.resizable-field.js" source for some customization of
    resizable textarea behaviour (providing "data-*" attrs to widget)

Example usage:
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
from django import forms
from django.contrib import admin
from sakkada.admin.editors.simplefb import SimpleFBTextarea


class SomeAdminForm(forms.ModelForm):
    class Meta:
        model = Some
        fields = '__all__'
        widgets = {'text': SimpleFBTextarea,}


class SomeAdmin(admin.ModelAdmin):
    form = SomeAdminForm


admin.site.register(Some, SomeAdmin)
